{"type": "user", "message": {"role": "user", "content": [{"tool_use_id": "chatcmpl-tool-a0672e4688ecec14", "type": "tool_result", "content": "# DashengTokenizer: One layer is enough for unified audio understanding and generation\narXiv: 2602.23765\nAuthors: Heinrich Dinkel, Xingwei Sun, Gang Li, Jiahao Mei, Yadong Niu, Jizhong Liu, Xiyang Li, Yifan Liao, Jiahao Zhou, Junbo Zhang, Jian Luan\nYear: 2026 | Venue: \nTopic: codec_vae\nStatus: unread\n\nContributions:\n  1. DashengTokenizer introduces a unified continuous audio tokenizer that embeds low-dimensional acoustic information into high-dimensional frozen semantic features via a simple linear projection.\n  2. The proposed acoustic injection method significantly outperforms previous audio codecs and encoders in linear evaluation across 22 diverse audio understanding tasks while maintaining competitive reconstruction quality.\n  3. A semantic preservation loss is introduced to prevent acoustic features from overwhelming semantic representations, effectively bridging the gap between understanding and generation.\n  4. The tokenizer achieves superior performance in speech enhancement, yielding higher objective quality and speaker similarity compared to existing encoder baselines.\n  5. DashengTokenizer surpasses standard VAE-based methods on text-to-audio and text-to-music generation tasks while also demonstrating significantly faster training convergence.\n  6. The results challenge the prevailing assumption that VAE-based architectures are a prerequisite for audio synthesis.\n\nTags: 压缩, 压缩/语义声学-语义, 压缩/语义声学-声学, 压缩/语义声学-混合\n---", "is_error": false}]}, "parent_tool_use_id": null, "session_id": "bce5716e-1fab-4972-8df9-11bb46f9f211", "uuid": "2dd2af84-fcae-4c5b-8f5b-af0ee3db477d", "timestamp": "2026-07-07T05:39:25.894Z", "tool_use_result": {"stdout": "# DashengTokenizer: One layer is enough for unified audio understanding and generation\narXiv: 2602.23765\nAuthors: Heinrich Dinkel, Xingwei Sun, Gang Li, Jiahao Mei, Yadong Niu, Jizhong Liu, Xiyang Li, Yifan Liao, Jiahao Zhou, Junbo Zhang, Jian Luan\nYear: 2026 | Venue: \nTopic: codec_vae\nStatus: unread\n\nContributions:\n  1. DashengTokenizer introduces a unified continuous audio tokenizer that embeds low-dimensional acoustic information into high-dimensional frozen semantic features via a simple linear projection.\n  2. The proposed acoustic injection method significantly outperforms previous audio codecs and encoders in linear evaluation across 22 diverse audio understanding tasks while maintaining competitive reconstruction quality.\n  3. A semantic preservation loss is introduced to prevent acoustic features from overwhelming semantic representations, effectively bridging the gap between understanding and generation.\n  4. The tokenizer achieves superior performance in speech enhancement, yielding higher objective quality and speaker similarity compared to existing encoder baselines.\n  5. DashengTokenizer surpasses standard VAE-based methods on text-to-audio and text-to-music generation tasks while also demonstrating significantly faster training convergence.\n  6. The results challenge the prevailing assumption that VAE-based architectures are a prerequisite for audio synthesis.\n\nTags: 压缩, 压缩/语义声学-语义, 压缩/语义声学-声学, 压缩/语义声学-混合\n---", "stderr": "", "interrupted": false, "isImage": false, "noOutputExpected": false}}
